WEBVTT

00:00.967 --> 00:03.033
♪ WHEN THIS BOY MEETS WORLD ♪

00:03.033 --> 00:06.000
♪ BOY MEETS WORLD ♪

00:06.000 --> 00:10.367
♪ WANDERIN' DOWN THIS ROAD
THAT WE CALL LIFE ♪

00:10.367 --> 00:12.667
♪ IS WHAT WE'RE DOIN' ♪

00:12.667 --> 00:14.500
♪ IT'S GOOD TO KNOW
I HAVE FRIENDS ♪

00:14.500 --> 00:16.300
♪ WHO WILL ALWAYS ♪

00:16.300 --> 00:18.734
♪ STAND BY ME ♪

00:18.734 --> 00:21.800
♪ WHEN THIS BOY MEETS WORLD ♪

00:21.800 --> 00:24.734
YOU'RE GONNA BE
A BEAUTIFUL BRIDE, TOPANGA.

00:24.734 --> 00:26.000
THANKS, MOM.

00:26.000 --> 00:28.567
I JUST WANT EVERYTHING
TO BE SO PERFECT FOR CORY.

00:28.567 --> 00:29.800
I LOVE HIM SO MUCH.

00:29.800 --> 00:32.200
THIS WHOLE DAY
IS JUST FULL OF LOVE!

00:32.200 --> 00:33.667
I HATE HIM!

00:33.667 --> 00:36.033
HE'S A SELF-CENTERED,
WHINING, DEMANDING,

00:36.033 --> 00:37.734
MISERABLE LITTLE WHITE BOY.

00:37.734 --> 00:39.567
WHAT HAPPENED,
MY BROTHER?

00:39.567 --> 00:41.867
"GET THE TUXEDOS,
PUMICE MY TOES,

00:41.867 --> 00:43.300
TIE THE CANS TO THE CAR!"

00:43.300 --> 00:45.600
I'M HIS BEST MAN,
NOT HIS HAMSTER!

00:45.600 --> 00:46.934
BUT YOU GOT THE TUXES?

00:46.934 --> 00:49.200
YOU TWO
DESERVE EACH OTHER.

00:49.200 --> 00:51.800
UM, SHAWN, WHAT IS
REALLY BOTHERING YOU?

00:51.800 --> 00:53.667
CORY
IS REALLY BOTHERING ME!

00:53.667 --> 00:55.967
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT I EVER SAW IN HIM.

00:55.967 --> 01:00.100
SHAWN...[LAUGHS]
SEE, THIS IS MY WEDDING DAY,

01:00.100 --> 01:03.300
AND I WOULD REALLY APPRECIATE IT
IF THERE WASN'T ANY TENSION.

01:03.300 --> 01:06.600
I DON'T CARE. IF SOMEBODY
ABUSES ME, I LASH OUT.

01:06.600 --> 01:08.200
NOBODY'S ABUSING ANYBODY.

01:08.200 --> 01:10.934
THIS IS MY WEDDING DAY.
HOW DARE YOU?

01:10.934 --> 01:12.700
COULD SOMEBODY
HELP ME OUT HERE, PLEASE?

01:12.700 --> 01:15.033
THE BEST MAN
CANNOT HATE THE GROOM.

01:15.033 --> 01:17.100
YOU'RE GONNA RUIN
MY WEDDING PICTURES.

01:17.100 --> 01:18.967
HONEY, YOU'RE KILLING HIM.

01:18.967 --> 01:20.367
DAD! I'M COMIN', DAD!

01:20.367 --> 01:23.400
TOPANGA, IF HE DIES,
THEN THE BEST MAN IS ERIC.

01:23.400 --> 01:25.567
THEN WE DON'T WANT HIM
TO DIE.

01:25.567 --> 01:26.800
NO. NO, WE DON'T.

01:26.800 --> 01:28.367
YOU OKAY? GOOD BOY.

01:28.367 --> 01:30.867
GOOD BOY.

01:30.867 --> 01:32.600
THEY'RE BOTH PSYCHO.

01:32.600 --> 01:34.867
HOW CAN THERE BE ANYTHING WRONG
BETWEEN YOU AND CORY?

01:34.867 --> 01:36.467
YOU LOVE HIM MORE THAN <i>I </i>DO.

01:36.467 --> 01:37.934
IT'S TRUE,
BUT I'M OKAY WITH IT.

01:40.200 --> 01:41.967
WHAT'S GOIN' ON?

01:41.967 --> 01:44.300
OUR ENTIRE FRIENDSHIP
HAS ALWAYS BEEN ABOUT HIM.

01:44.300 --> 01:47.300
HOW DOES <i>CORY </i>FEEL?
WHAT IS <i>CORY </i>THINKING?

01:47.300 --> 01:49.100
COME ON, SHAWN,
WHAT'S THIS REALLY ABOUT?

01:49.100 --> 01:50.967
YOU KNOW...

01:50.967 --> 01:53.000
YOU THINK ON HIS WEDDING DAY,

01:53.000 --> 01:55.100
HE'D REALIZE
HOW HARD THIS IS FOR ME.

02:02.500 --> 02:04.800
WHERE'S MY BEST MAN?
DON'T KNOW.

02:04.800 --> 02:06.667
SHOULD'VE PICKED ME!
HE'S NOT HERE YET?

02:06.667 --> 02:08.934
I'M GETTIN' MARRIED
IN FOUR HOURS!

02:08.934 --> 02:10.367
IT'S TIME
FOR THE OLDER BROTHER

02:10.367 --> 02:12.567
TO GIVE THE YOUNGER BROTHER
THE PREWEDDING SEX TALK.

02:12.567 --> 02:13.900
[ Sarcastically ]
OH, GOODY.

02:15.100 --> 02:18.000
YOU? I'M GETTIN' ADVICE
FROM <i>YOU? </i>

02:18.000 --> 02:19.900
TAKE NOTES, MOMMY.
ERIC MATTHEWS IS GIVIN' LESSONS.

02:21.767 --> 02:24.934
OH, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.

02:24.934 --> 02:28.600
LESSON ONE: SEX WITHOUT LOVE
IS EMPTY AND HOLLOW.

02:28.600 --> 02:30.834
AND THAT'S JUST
THE WAY WE MEN LIKE IT.

02:34.467 --> 02:38.667
ERIC, YOU'RE COMPLETELY MISSING
THE BEAUTY OF HUMAN SEXUALITY.

02:38.667 --> 02:40.567
IT'S NOT JUST A PHYSICAL ACT.

02:40.567 --> 02:42.900
IT'S THE INTIMACY
BETWEEN TWO PEOPLE,

02:42.900 --> 02:44.500
SHARING THEIR SOULS.

02:44.500 --> 02:47.200
MAYBE FOR OLD PEOPLE.

02:47.200 --> 02:50.600
YOU KNOW, YOU'RE ALL CRAZY.

02:50.600 --> 02:52.900
I CAN'T BELIEVE SHAWN!
I CAN'T BELIEVE HE'S NOT HERE!

02:52.900 --> 02:55.500
WHAT IS SO HARD
ABOUT REMEMBERING THE TUXEDOS,

02:55.500 --> 02:57.500
THE WEDDING CAKE,
AND THE RINGS?!

02:57.500 --> 02:59.667
FIRE SHAWN.
YOU KNOW YOU WANT TO.

02:59.667 --> 03:00.934
C'MON, GIVE ME THE JOB.
I'M YOUR BROTHER.

03:00.934 --> 03:02.900
WE BOTH CAME OUT OF
OUR DADDY'S WOMB.

03:02.900 --> 03:04.967
CORY, YOU AND SHAWN
ARE BEST FRIENDS,

03:04.967 --> 03:07.400
AND YOU'RE GOING TO <i>STAY  </i>
BEST FRIENDS.

03:07.400 --> 03:09.200
ARE WE?
WHAT?

03:09.200 --> 03:11.600
BECAUSE WHERE IS MY BEST FRIEND
WITH THE TUXEDOS?

03:11.600 --> 03:14.400
WHY IS MY BEST FRIEND TRYING
TO SABOTAGE MY WEDDING DAY?

03:14.400 --> 03:16.133
NOW I'M SABOTAGING
YOUR WEDDING DAY?

03:16.133 --> 03:17.400
WHERE ARE THE TUXEDOS?

03:17.400 --> 03:18.600
I DON'T HAVE THEM YET.

03:18.600 --> 03:19.734
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

03:19.734 --> 03:21.734
I'VE BEEN TYING TIN CANS
TO THE VOLVO

03:21.734 --> 03:22.767
FOR THE LAST HOUR.

03:22.767 --> 03:24.233
MY FINGERS ARE BLEEDING.

03:24.233 --> 03:25.467
WE DON'T HAVE A VOLVO.

03:26.500 --> 03:27.600
WE HAVE A CHEVY.

03:27.600 --> 03:28.834
WHO HAS A VOLVO?

03:28.834 --> 03:30.934
WHO'S BEEN TYING CANS
TO MY CAR?

03:30.934 --> 03:31.967
HE DID.

03:31.967 --> 03:33.400
THIS IS TOO MUCH PRESSURE.

03:33.400 --> 03:36.767
WHAT'S THE MATTER?
YOU'RE LETTIN' ME DOWN.

03:36.767 --> 03:39.800
CORY, HAS IT OCCURRED TO YOU
EVEN A LITTLE BIT

03:39.800 --> 03:43.300
THAT, AS FAR AS YOU AND ME GO,
TODAY IS THE LAST DAY

03:43.300 --> 03:46.100
THAT WE'RE EVER GONNA BE
"CORY AND SHAWN"?

03:46.100 --> 03:48.300
YOU KNOW? "SHAWN AND CORY"?

03:53.200 --> 03:55.734
BEANS.
YOU PICKED BEANS?!

03:55.734 --> 03:56.734
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

03:56.734 --> 04:00.200
BEANS ARE NOT A WEDDING CAN!
WHY NOT?

04:00.200 --> 04:02.867
BEANS DO NOT SAY
"ETERNAL LOVE AND HAPPINESS"!

04:02.867 --> 04:03.867
I KNOW WHAT THEY SAY!

04:03.867 --> 04:05.900
I'M TRYIN' TO TALK TO YOU.

04:05.900 --> 04:07.934
I DON'T WANNA TALK
ABOUT IT NOW.
WHY NOT?!

04:07.934 --> 04:10.400
DID YOU PICK UP THE HONEYMOON
TICKETS FROM THE TRAVEL AGENT?

04:10.400 --> 04:11.400
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

04:11.400 --> 04:12.400
GUYS!

04:12.400 --> 04:13.834
NO, NO, NO.
DAD, PLEASE!

04:13.834 --> 04:15.300
I JUST WANT A GUY

04:15.300 --> 04:18.100
WHO CAN PICK UP THE TUXEDOS
AND TIE SOME CANS TOGETHER.

04:18.100 --> 04:19.834
I JUST WANNA TALK TO YOU
ABOUT THIS.

04:19.834 --> 04:22.200
I JUST WANT
A COMPETENT BEST MAN!

04:22.200 --> 04:24.567
THEN GET A NEW ONE!

04:24.567 --> 04:27.300
WHAT DID YOU SAY?!
I SAID,
"GET A NEW BEST MAN"!

04:31.500 --> 04:34.133
UH! CORY, WHAT I THINK
WE'VE GOT HERE

04:34.133 --> 04:35.800
IS A BEST MAN
WHO'S FOLDED UNDER THE PRESSURE.

04:35.800 --> 04:37.367
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

04:37.367 --> 04:39.500
I'LL PICK UP THE TUXEDOS.
I'LL TIE THE CANS TO THE SUBARU.

04:39.500 --> 04:41.600
IT'S ALL TAKEN CARE OF.

04:43.667 --> 04:45.700
YOU CAN BE AN USHER.

04:45.700 --> 04:46.800
I DON'T WANNA BE AN USHER.

04:46.800 --> 04:49.567
YOU WANNA WALK
NANA BOO BOO DOWN THE AISLE?

04:49.567 --> 04:51.834
I DON'T WANNA WALK
NANA BOO BOO ANYWHERE.

04:51.834 --> 04:53.600
WHAT DO YOU WANNA DO, SHAWN?

04:53.600 --> 04:55.500
I DON'T WANNA DO ANYTHING.

04:55.500 --> 04:58.467
YOU DON'T WANT TO DO ANYTHING
AT MY WEDDING?!

04:58.467 --> 05:00.066
NO, I'M <i>NOT </i>GOING
TO YOUR WEDDING!

05:00.066 --> 05:02.200
FINE! THEN DON'T GO!

05:14.233 --> 05:17.000
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.
I JUST SPOKE TO SHAWN,

05:17.000 --> 05:18.800
AND I'M SURE
HE'LL FORGIVE YOU

05:18.800 --> 05:20.500
IF YOU JUST GIVE HIM A CALL.

05:20.500 --> 05:24.000
SHAWN CAN KISS MY GROOM
<i>TUCHES </i>IN HELL.

05:24.000 --> 05:27.800
MIRROR, MIRROR, ON THE WALL,
WHO'S THE BEST BEST MAN OF ALL?

05:27.800 --> 05:30.100
[ High-pitched voice ]
YOU ARE, ERIC. YOU ARE.

05:30.100 --> 05:32.867
HEY, MORON,
WHERE ARE THE TUXEDOS?

05:32.867 --> 05:34.600
[ Normal voice ]
IN THE LIMO, BABY.

05:34.600 --> 05:35.967
WHAT LIMO, BABY?

05:35.967 --> 05:37.734
THE LIMO THAT'S TAKING US
TO CORY'S WEDDING.

05:37.734 --> 05:40.767
YOU DON'T THINK I'D LET HIM GET
MARRIED IN <i>THIS </i>DUMP, DO YOU?

05:40.767 --> 05:43.767
WHAT DID YOU DO?
NO TIME, MOM.
WE'RE ON A SCHEDULE.

05:43.767 --> 05:46.000
THE GIRLS ARE ON THEIR WAY,
SO WE GOTTA MOVE.

05:47.233 --> 05:49.300
WE GOTTA MOVE, PEOPLE!
MOVE, PEOPLE!

05:49.300 --> 05:52.900
NICE LEGS, FEENY.

05:52.900 --> 05:55.100
TELL SHAWN MY NEW BEST MAN
GOT ME A LIMO.

05:55.100 --> 05:56.967
BEFORE OR AFTER
THE GROOM <i>TUCHES </i>IN HELL?

05:56.967 --> 05:58.133
YOU DECIDE.

05:58.133 --> 06:00.300
IS THIS GONNA BE
VERY, <i>VERY </i>BAD?

06:00.300 --> 06:01.800
WE'LL SEE.

06:11.667 --> 06:17.300
ERIC, THIS IS THE PHILADELPHIA
VICTORIAN HOTEL!

06:17.300 --> 06:19.233
<i>VERY </i>NICE!

06:19.233 --> 06:20.500
THIS IS AN ERIC THING.

06:20.500 --> 06:22.767
[ Nervously ]
THIS IS AN ERIC THING.

06:22.767 --> 06:24.200
I'M NOT PAYIN' FOR THIS.

06:24.200 --> 06:26.500
YOU NEVER MADE ANY
<i>REAL </i>MONEY, DID YOU, DAD?

06:26.500 --> 06:29.133
NO, BUT I HAD YOU,
SO I'M TWICE CURSED.

06:30.300 --> 06:31.934
ERIC, WHAT IS THE DEAL HERE?

06:31.934 --> 06:34.300
THIS IS THE MOST IMPORTANT DAY
IN MY LITTLE BROTHER'S LIFE,

06:34.300 --> 06:35.500
AND I CAME THROUGH.

06:35.500 --> 06:38.867
SO EITHER
YOU CAN HAVE A GREAT TIME

06:38.867 --> 06:40.300
OR YOU CAN BE ALL CYNICAL

06:40.300 --> 06:42.567
AND THINK SOMETHING FISHY
IS GOING ON.

06:42.567 --> 06:46.000
IS EVERYTHING TO YOUR
SATISFACTION, MR. PETERMAN?

06:46.000 --> 06:47.700
INDEED IT IS...

06:48.867 --> 06:50.800
...MR. PETERMAN.

06:50.800 --> 06:52.800
YOU LET US KNOW
IF YOU NEED <i>ANYTHING, </i>

06:52.800 --> 06:55.100
MR. PETERMAN.

06:55.100 --> 06:57.767
OKAY. GO AWAY NOW.
GO -- GO AWAY.

06:57.767 --> 06:59.133
BYE-BYE.

06:59.133 --> 07:01.400
[ CHUCKLES ]

07:01.400 --> 07:04.934
WHY YOU ALL LOOKIN' AT ME?!

07:04.934 --> 07:07.934
DO YOU THINK ANYTHING'S GONNA
CHANGE AFTER I GET MARRIED?

07:07.934 --> 07:09.667
NO. NOTHING
IS GONNA CHANGE.

07:09.667 --> 07:12.500
JUST BECAUSE YOU'RE MOVING OUT,
AND YOU'RE SETTING UP HOUSE,

07:12.500 --> 07:14.667
AND YOU'RE GONNA BE WITH CORY
ALL THE TIME

07:14.667 --> 07:16.200
AND MAYBE HAVE KIDS SOMEDAY --

07:16.200 --> 07:18.500
GOSH, I AM NEVER
GONNA SEE YOU AGAIN, AM I?

07:18.500 --> 07:20.467
OHH.OHH.

07:20.467 --> 07:22.000
DO YOU WANT ME
TO CALL IT OFF?

07:22.000 --> 07:24.000
I WANT YOU TO BE HAPPY.

07:24.000 --> 07:25.934
I WANT YOU
TO BE HAPPY, TOO.

07:25.934 --> 07:28.700
I WANT YOU
TO BE HAPPY <i>THREE! </i>

07:28.700 --> 07:31.400
YOU'RE GETTING MARRIED
TODAY!

07:31.400 --> 07:32.834
AHHH!
AHHH!
AHHH!

07:32.834 --> 07:35.767
[ PLAYING CLASSICAL MUSIC ]

08:06.900 --> 08:11.567
<i>YOU </i>ARE VERY HOT.

08:15.567 --> 08:17.000
Thanks.

08:20.567 --> 08:22.800
Hey, ring boy...

08:22.800 --> 08:24.233
where are the rings?

08:24.233 --> 08:28.300
THAT'S YOUR JOB, SLICK.
I'M JUST HERE TO LOOK CUTE.

08:30.467 --> 08:32.600
[ Laughing ]
IT'S OKAY.

08:32.600 --> 08:35.000
YOU FORGOT THE RINGS,
DIDN'T YOU?

08:35.000 --> 08:36.934
YES, BUT I REMEMBERED
MY UNDERWEAR!

08:36.934 --> 08:38.000
OKAY.

08:38.000 --> 08:39.100
NO, I DIDN'T!

08:41.000 --> 08:45.567
[ BAND PLAYS MENDELSSOHN'S
"WEDDING MARCH" ]

09:12.200 --> 09:16.200
BE GOOD TO EACH OTHER.

09:19.800 --> 09:23.600
WE'VE WAITED FOR THIS MOMENT
ALL OUR LIVES.

09:23.600 --> 09:25.834
WHAT ARE YOU THINKING?

09:25.834 --> 09:29.200
I CAN'T BELIEVE
SHAWN'S NOT HERE.

09:29.200 --> 09:32.467
I LOVE YOU, TOO.

09:39.300 --> 09:42.734
DEARLY BELOVED,
WE ARE GATHERED HERE TODAY

09:42.734 --> 09:47.133
TO WITNESS THE WEDDING
OF MYRA AND HAROLD.

09:49.100 --> 09:50.834
JUST KEEP GOIN'.
JUST KEEP GOIN'.

09:52.900 --> 09:57.867
AND NOW, A SONG
FROM THE MOTHER OF THE GROOM,

09:57.867 --> 10:00.567
MRS. FLORENCE PETERMAN.

10:00.567 --> 10:02.000
I THINK THAT'S YOU.

10:06.467 --> 10:09.467
[ PLAYS INTRODUCTION ]

10:11.500 --> 10:16.467
♪ I LOVE YOU TRULY ♪

10:16.467 --> 10:21.133
♪ TRULY, DEAR... ♪

10:21.133 --> 10:24.767
HEY, YOU'RE GONNA NEED
THESE RINGS.

10:24.767 --> 10:26.200
I KNEW YOU'D COME.

10:26.200 --> 10:27.734
I WOULDN'T MISS THIS, CORY.

10:27.734 --> 10:30.767
LOOK, I AM SO SORRY
FOR ALL THE STUFF THAT HAPPENED.

10:30.767 --> 10:33.100
WELL, YOU SHOULD BE,
BUT WE'LL TALK ABOUT IT

10:33.100 --> 10:35.300
AFTER YOU GET BACK
FROM THE HONEYMOON, OKAY?

10:35.300 --> 10:36.400
WAIT A MINUTE.

10:36.400 --> 10:38.734
WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
<i>I </i>SHOULD BE?

10:38.734 --> 10:41.400
CORY, YOU'VE BEEN
BEING A JERK TO ME.

10:41.400 --> 10:43.700
THAT'S BECAUSE YOU'RE THE ONE
THAT FORGOT THE TUXEDOS,

10:43.700 --> 10:45.800
AND YOU'RE THE ONE
THAT DIDN'T TIE THE TIN CANS.

10:45.800 --> 10:47.967
IT'S LIKE YOU'RE TRYING
TO SABOTAGE MY WEDDING DAY!

10:47.967 --> 10:49.600
THAT IS RIDICULOUS!

10:49.600 --> 10:53.133
IF I WANTED TO SABOTAGE
YOUR WEDDING DAY,

10:53.133 --> 10:54.367
I'D DO THIS.

10:54.367 --> 10:56.567
OH.

10:56.567 --> 10:57.834
HA HA HA.

10:57.834 --> 10:59.200
BOY, OH, BOY.

10:59.200 --> 11:03.400
YOU, UH,
YOU DO NOT WANNA DO THAT.

11:03.400 --> 11:05.400
GET HIM, TOPANGA!

11:05.400 --> 11:06.767
YOU KNOW WHAT?

11:06.767 --> 11:10.233
I SHOULDN'T HAVE COME HERE.
HAVE A WONDERFUL LIFE, JERK.

11:10.233 --> 11:13.400
YOU, TOO, TRAILER TRASH!

11:13.400 --> 11:14.834
OOOHH!

11:14.834 --> 11:16.000
SHAWN'S POOR!

11:16.000 --> 11:18.600
HA HA HA HA HA HA HA!

11:18.600 --> 11:20.200
[ MUSIC AND SINGING STOP ]

11:20.200 --> 11:22.300
AHHHHHHH!

11:22.300 --> 11:24.600
Alan: HEY, HEY, HEY!

11:24.600 --> 11:26.734
THIS IS MY WEDDING DAY!

11:26.734 --> 11:29.100
I'VE WAITED...
MY WHOLE...

11:29.100 --> 11:32.200
TRY NOT TO USE THE WORD
"PETERMAN" ANYMORE, ALL RIGHT?

11:32.200 --> 11:35.233
HE DOESN'T CARE THAT WE'RE
NOT GONNA BE FRIENDS ANYMORE!

11:35.233 --> 11:36.600
WHY DO YOU
KEEP SAYIN' THAT?!

11:36.600 --> 11:38.300
WHY DO YOU KEEP
BRINGING THAT UP?!

11:38.300 --> 11:40.000
BECAUSE YOU WON'T TALK
ABOUT IT!

11:40.000 --> 11:41.300
I DON'T WANNA TALK ABOUT IT!

11:41.300 --> 11:43.100
WHY DO YOU THINK I'VE BEEN
SENDING YOU EVERYWHERE?!

11:43.100 --> 11:45.200
WE <i>HAVE </i>TO TALK ABOUT IT!

11:45.200 --> 11:48.033
[ Crying ]
I DON'T WANT TO!

11:48.033 --> 11:50.667
[ Crying ]
WE <i>HAVE </i>TO!

11:50.667 --> 11:52.767
NOW?!

11:55.033 --> 11:56.300
CORY...

11:56.300 --> 12:00.200
AFTER YOU GET MARRIED,
THINGS ARE GONNA BE DIFFERENT,

12:00.200 --> 12:04.367
AND I DON'T HAVE
A LOT OF FRIENDS, YOU KNOW?

12:07.700 --> 12:13.300
SHAWNIE, I -- I DON'T KNOW
WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN.

12:13.300 --> 12:17.600
WHAT DO YOU WANT ME TO DO?

12:17.600 --> 12:21.700
I DON'T KNOW.

12:21.700 --> 12:26.000
DO YOU REALLY LIKE HER?

12:26.000 --> 12:29.834
YEAH, I REALLY DO.

12:29.834 --> 12:32.800
YOU SURE?

12:32.800 --> 12:34.500
SHAWN...

12:34.500 --> 12:39.867
I REALLY THINK I'VE BEEN <i>VERY </i>
TOLERANT HERE.

12:39.867 --> 12:43.600
OKAY...

12:43.600 --> 12:45.100
MARRY HER.

12:45.100 --> 12:48.233
YOU'RE GIVING ME
YOUR BLESSING?

12:48.233 --> 12:54.000
YEAH, WELL...
WE GOTTA GROW UP SOMETIME.

12:57.467 --> 13:01.000
I WASN'T SURE
THIS DAY WOULD EVER COME,

13:01.000 --> 13:02.467
BUT YOU WERE.

13:02.467 --> 13:04.767
I WASN'T SURE
THAT LOVE COULD SURVIVE

13:04.767 --> 13:07.000
EVERYTHING
THAT WE PUT IT THROUGH,

13:07.000 --> 13:09.100
BUT YOU WERE.

13:09.100 --> 13:12.400
YOU WERE ALWAYS STRONG
AND ALWAYS SURE.

13:12.400 --> 13:13.867
AND NOW I KNOW

13:13.867 --> 13:18.000
THAT I WANT YOU TO STAND BESIDE
ME FOR THE REST OF MY LIFE.

13:18.000 --> 13:20.867
THAT'S WHAT I'M SURE OF.

13:25.500 --> 13:29.200
I HAVE TO TALK
TO <i>HER </i>NOW, OKAY?

13:29.200 --> 13:30.300
GO AHEAD.

13:30.300 --> 13:31.300
OKAY.

13:34.700 --> 13:38.033
UM...

13:38.033 --> 13:40.400
EVER SINCE I WAS YOUNG,

13:40.400 --> 13:45.400
I NEVER REALLY UNDERSTOOD
ANYTHING ABOUT THE WORLD,

13:45.400 --> 13:50.967
AND I NEVER UNDERSTOOD ANYTHING
THAT HAPPENED IN MY LIFE.

13:50.967 --> 13:53.000
THE ONLY THING

13:53.000 --> 13:57.000
THAT EVER MADE SENSE TO ME
WAS YOU

13:57.000 --> 13:59.500
AND HOW I FELT ABOUT YOU.

14:02.000 --> 14:06.500
THAT'S...ALL I'VE EVER KNOWN

14:06.500 --> 14:09.500
AND THAT'S ENOUGH.

14:09.500 --> 14:13.700
THAT'S ENOUGH FOR ME FOR
THE REST OF MY LIFE, TOPANGA.

14:16.767 --> 14:19.233
WE GONNA GET MARRIED?

14:19.233 --> 14:21.467
YEAH, WE ARE.

14:21.467 --> 14:23.200
GOOD, GOOD,

14:23.200 --> 14:28.834
'CAUSE [SNIFFLES]
UM, I HAVE THESE RINGS.

14:32.200 --> 14:34.367
I LOVE YOU, TOPANGA.

14:34.367 --> 14:36.667
I LOVE YOU, TOO, CORY.

14:38.900 --> 14:41.367
[ SNIFFLES ]

14:46.300 --> 14:48.233
Minister:
DO YOU TAKE THIS MAN

14:48.233 --> 14:50.467
TO BE
YOUR LAWFULLY WEDDED HUSBAND,

14:50.467 --> 14:52.834
TO HAVE AND TO HOLD,
TO CHERISH AND ADORE,

14:52.834 --> 14:54.400
FROM THIS DAY FORWARD,

14:54.400 --> 15:00.066
IN SICKNESS AND IN HEALTH,
AS LONG AS YOU BOTH SHALL LIVE?

15:00.066 --> 15:03.000
I DO.

15:03.000 --> 15:06.233
AND DO YOU TAKE THIS WOMAN
TO BE YOUR LAWFULLY WEDDED WIFE,

15:06.233 --> 15:08.600
TO HAVE AND TO HOLD,
TO CHERISH AND ADORE,

15:08.600 --> 15:10.200
FROM THIS DAY FORWARD,

15:10.200 --> 15:16.700
IN SICKNESS AND IN HEALTH,
AS LONG AS YOU BOTH SHALL LIVE?

15:16.700 --> 15:19.500
I DO.

15:19.500 --> 15:21.567
THEN BY THE POWER VESTED IN ME

15:21.567 --> 15:24.200
BY THE COMMONWEALTH
OF PENNSYLVANIA,

15:24.200 --> 15:27.033
I NOW PRONOUNCE YOU
HUSBAND AND WIFE.

15:27.033 --> 15:29.400
YOU MAY KISS THE BRIDE.

15:29.400 --> 15:31.734
MMM.

15:33.400 --> 15:34.734
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,

15:34.734 --> 15:36.700
FAMILY AND FRIENDS,

15:36.700 --> 15:39.734
I PRESENT TO YOU
FOR THE FIRST TIME EVER --

15:39.734 --> 15:44.467
MR. AND MRS. HAROLD PETERMAN.

15:44.467 --> 15:46.934
[ LIGHT APPLAUSE ]

15:46.934 --> 15:48.600
IT'S OKAY! HAROLD!

16:02.467 --> 16:05.400
MAYBE WE COULD GO
SOMEWHERE LATER.

16:07.767 --> 16:09.300
MR. FEENY, HELP.

16:11.400 --> 16:14.900
SCRAM, ZIPPY.

16:14.900 --> 16:16.834
THIS WAS AN AMAZING WEDDING.

16:16.834 --> 16:17.967
IT'S FABULOUS.

16:17.967 --> 16:20.900
HOW COULD ERIC
HAVE PULLED THIS THING OFF?

16:20.900 --> 16:23.000
THAT'S THE FIRST THING
I'LL ASK HIM

16:23.000 --> 16:24.767
WHEN I VISIT HIM IN ATTICA.

16:24.767 --> 16:27.834
EXCUSE ME.
MAY WE CUT IN?

16:27.834 --> 16:29.100
YES.

16:31.500 --> 16:34.367
CORY, I'M SO PROUD OF YOU.

16:34.367 --> 16:36.300
THANK YOU, MAMA.

16:36.300 --> 16:38.867
AND EVEN THOUGH
YOU'RE A MARRIED MAN NOW,

16:38.867 --> 16:43.300
YOU ARE STILL OUR LITTLE BOY,
AND WE LOVE YOU VERY MUCH.

16:43.300 --> 16:47.300
AND WHEN HE MAKES YOU NUTS,
YOU CALL <i>ME. </i>

16:47.300 --> 16:49.834
THANKS...DAD.

16:49.834 --> 16:52.000
[ GLASS CLINKING ]

16:52.000 --> 16:53.767
I'D LIKE TO PROPOSE A TOAST.

16:57.100 --> 17:00.767
[ SIGHS ]
THIS IS FOR HAROLD AND MYRA.

17:00.767 --> 17:03.667
WHAT'S UP WITH THAT, ERIC?

17:03.667 --> 17:04.767
NOTHIN'.

17:04.767 --> 17:07.233
JUST TALK FAST, ALL RIGHT?

17:07.233 --> 17:10.100
WELL, THERE IS SOMETHING
I'D LIKE TO SAY.

17:10.100 --> 17:13.767
I MAY NOT BE THE BEST MAN,
BUT I AM THE BEST FRIEND.

17:13.767 --> 17:17.200
CORY AND I HAVE BEEN
BEST FRIENDS ALL OUR LIVES.

17:17.200 --> 17:20.000
AND, UM,

17:20.000 --> 17:22.233
THIS WEDDING'S BEEN
KIND OF HARD FOR ME

17:22.233 --> 17:23.600
BECAUSE I KNOW,

17:23.600 --> 17:26.100
NO MATTER HOW MUCH
WE MAY AVOID TALKING ABOUT IT,

17:26.100 --> 17:29.467
CORY AND I AREN'T GONNA BE
BEST FRIENDS FOREVER.

17:29.467 --> 17:32.500
THINGS ARE CHANGING
BETWEEN US.

17:32.500 --> 17:35.467
THINGS HAVE ALWAYS
BEEN CHANGING.

17:35.467 --> 17:39.233
WE'VE HAD TO DEAL
WITH LIFE AND DEATH

17:39.233 --> 17:43.967
AND FEENY.

17:43.967 --> 17:47.800
BUT NO MATTER WHAT WE FACED,
WE ALWAYS FACED IT TOGETHER.

17:47.800 --> 17:51.500
SO, THEN, HOW CAN WE POSSIBLY
BE UPSET WITH EACH OTHER

17:51.500 --> 17:53.400
ON HIS WEDDING DAY?

17:53.400 --> 17:56.233
WELL, IT'S BECAUSE DEEP DOWN,

17:56.233 --> 17:59.200
I THINK CORY AND I BOTH KNOW

17:59.200 --> 18:02.900
THAT WE'RE NOT GONNA BE
BEST FRIENDS ANYMORE.

18:05.700 --> 18:10.000
AND THAT'S THE WAY
IT <i>SHOULD </i>BE.

18:10.000 --> 18:13.200
SO THIS IS TO TOPANGA --

18:13.200 --> 18:15.467
CORY'S WIFE...

18:15.467 --> 18:18.500
AND NEW BEST FRIEND.

18:21.367 --> 18:24.867
[ Voice breaking ]
TAKE CARE OF HIM, OKAY?

18:24.867 --> 18:26.967
[ Crying ] I WILL.

18:26.967 --> 18:30.600
AND WHEN HE MAKES YOU NUTS,
CALL ME.

18:30.600 --> 18:33.000
I WILL.

18:35.367 --> 18:37.800
TO CORY AND TOPANGA!

18:37.800 --> 18:40.400
All: CORY AND TOPANGA!

18:40.400 --> 18:45.467
AND NOW...
I WOULD LIKE TO GIVE MY GIFT

18:45.467 --> 18:49.100
TO MY LITTLE BROTHER
AND NEW SISTER-IN-LAW.

18:49.100 --> 18:52.767
ERIC, THIS WEDDING
WAS MORE THAN ENOUGH.

18:52.767 --> 18:54.400
YEAH, IT WAS, WASN'T IT?

18:54.400 --> 18:57.467
BUT I DO HAVE
ONE MORE THING UP MY SLEEVE.

18:57.467 --> 19:00.200
I HOLD IN MY HAND A KEY --

19:00.200 --> 19:03.000
A KEY TO THE HONEYMOON SUITE

19:03.000 --> 19:05.700
OF THE PHILADELPHIA
VICTORIA HOTEL.

19:05.700 --> 19:07.367
SO THAT AFTER THIS --

19:07.367 --> 19:08.300
BYE!

19:08.300 --> 19:09.767
WHOO!
BYE!

19:10.934 --> 19:12.000
ALL RIGHT!

19:14.600 --> 19:16.867
ALL RIGHT.
ALL RIGHT, ERIC.

19:16.867 --> 19:18.700
YOU SPILL IT RIGHT NOW.

19:18.700 --> 19:21.934
Angela: HOW COULD YOU
POSSIBLY ARRANGE ALL THIS?

19:21.934 --> 19:23.500
OH, IT WAS CHILD'S PLAY.

19:23.500 --> 19:26.400
I'M PICKIN' UP THE TUXES,
AND I SEE THEY'RE SETTIN' UP

19:26.400 --> 19:28.800
FOR THIS HOITY-TOITY
PETERMAN WEDDING.

19:28.800 --> 19:30.400
THE DISPOSABLE DIAPER
PETERMANS?

19:30.400 --> 19:32.000
YEAH, THEM PETERMANS.

19:32.000 --> 19:34.300
THEIR WEDDING IS
THE SOCIAL EVENT OF THE YEAR.

19:34.300 --> 19:36.900
YEAH, WELL, NOW IT'S NOT.

19:36.900 --> 19:38.934
WHAT DID YOU DO?

19:38.934 --> 19:40.800
I JUST WENT OUT
TO THE PAY PHONE,

19:40.800 --> 19:42.133
AND I CALLED THE OPERATOR.

19:42.133 --> 19:44.100
SHE SAID, "WHAT HOTEL?"
AND I TOLD HER.

19:44.100 --> 19:45.600
WHILE SHE WAS GETTIN'
THE NUMBER,

19:45.600 --> 19:48.300
I LOOKED DOWN AT THE RECEIVER,
AND THERE WAS SCHMUTZ ON IT.

19:48.300 --> 19:50.300
I'M NOT SURE
IF IT WAS DRIED VOMIT OR GUM.

19:50.300 --> 19:51.700
IT TASTED MORE LIKE GUM --

19:51.700 --> 19:54.033
GET ON WITH IT!

19:54.033 --> 19:56.367
I TOLD THEM
THAT I WAS E.J. PETERMAN,

19:56.367 --> 19:58.934
AND I HAD TO GET MY DAUGHTER
MARRIED SOONER

19:58.934 --> 20:00.567
BECAUSE SHE WAS PREGNANT.

20:00.567 --> 20:02.467
SO DRINK UP, GUYS!

20:02.467 --> 20:07.467
'CAUSE IT'S GONNA HIT THE FAN
IN ABOUT, LIKE, TWO SECONDS.

20:07.467 --> 20:09.500
WHAT KIND
OF UNBELIEVABLE HOTEL MORON

20:09.500 --> 20:11.667
WOULD FALL FOR SOMETHING
THAT STUPID?

20:11.667 --> 20:15.233
MMMM...HIM.

20:21.934 --> 20:25.467
[ As Franck
from "Father of the Bride" ]
IS EVERYTHING SATISFACTORY?

20:25.467 --> 20:26.467
OH, QUITE, QUITE.

20:26.467 --> 20:28.667
YOU RUN A TIGHT SHIP HERE,
YOUNG FELLOW,

20:28.667 --> 20:30.300
AND YOU'RE
A GOOD-LOOKING MAN.

20:30.300 --> 20:32.400
Man: WHAT THE HELL
IS GOING ON HERE?!

20:33.600 --> 20:36.133
UH-OH.

20:37.667 --> 20:40.033
I'M E.J. PETERMAN.

20:40.033 --> 20:41.367
PARTY'S OVER, ISN'T IT?

20:41.367 --> 20:45.200
AND I DEMAND TO KNOW
WHAT THE HELL IS GOING ON HERE!

20:45.200 --> 20:46.667
OH YEAH, IT'S OVER.

20:46.667 --> 20:47.867
[WHISTLES]

20:47.867 --> 20:49.567
RUN LIKE HELL!

20:54.300 --> 20:56.734
MR. PETERMAN,
THERE WAS A WEDDING --

20:56.734 --> 21:00.734
I KNOW THERE WAS A WEDDING,
BUT IT WAS NOT <i>MY </i>WEDDING!

21:00.734 --> 21:02.567
SOMEONE COME IN
AND THEY GET MARRIED!

21:02.567 --> 21:04.867
THEY SAY "I DO"
WITH THE RING...

21:04.867 --> 21:07.033
IT'S MY DAUGHTER
I PAID FOR...

21:07.033 --> 21:09.567
YOU COME IN AT ME ALL --
DON'T WITH THE HANDS!

21:09.567 --> 21:11.033
PUT THE HANDS DOWN!

21:11.033 --> 21:13.800
DON'T EVEN START WITH ME
WITH THE ASCOT. WHO DRESS YOU?

21:13.800 --> 21:16.934
I'M GONNA GET
A HEART ATTACK HERE!

21:16.934 --> 21:18.967
YOU GO AHEAD
AND HAVE A HEART ATTACK!

21:18.967 --> 21:20.667
I NOT EVEN PICK UP
AFTER YOU!

21:20.667 --> 21:22.367
I NOT EVEN PICK UP
AFTER YOU!

21:22.367 --> 21:23.867
YOU GO SEE THE MANAGER.

21:23.867 --> 21:26.400
HE'S A LITTLE, SKIMPY GUY
WHO NEVER TIPS.
